# For more info on HTTP files go to https://aka.ms/vs/httpfile
@address = https://localhost:7115

### 1. Hello World - smoke test
GET {{address}}/

### 2. List books (empty or seeded)
GET {{address}}/books

### 3. List books with pagination (skip & take)
GET {{address}}/books?skip=0&take=10

### 4. List books with negative skip (should clamp to 0)
GET {{address}}/books?skip=-5&take=5

### 5. Create a new book
# @name createBook
POST {{address}}/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "5AM Club",
  "price": 1300
}

### 6. Get the created book by id
GET {{address}}/books/{{createBook.response.body.$.id}}

### 7. Update the created book
PUT {{address}}/books/{{createBook.response.body.$.id}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Monk Who Sold His Ferrari",
  "price": 1500
}

### 8. Verify the update
GET {{address}}/books/{{createBook.response.body.$.id}}

### 9. Delete the created book
DELETE {{address}}/books/{{createBook.response.body.$.id}}

### 10. Verify deletion (should return 404)
GET {{address}}/books/{{createBook.response.body.$.id}}

### 11. Get a non-existent book (should return 404)
GET {{address}}/books/00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000000

### 12. Create with missing title (should return 400 - validation)
POST {{address}}/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "",
  "price": 100
}

### 13. Create with negative price (should return 400 - validation)
POST {{address}}/books
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Test Book",
  "price": -10
}
